    <h3>Basic Concepts</h3>
    <br>
    <p>By default <i>My Ching</i> only displays the primary and
      resulting <i>(relating)</i> hexagram in a reading. This is
      sufficient for a basic I Ching consultation that will satisfy most
      people. However for those who desire a more in-depth reading,
      there are a number of auxiliary hexagrams that can be derived from
      the basic reading by analyzing the placement of changing lines. <i>My



        Ching</i> provides the ones described by I Ching scholar Stephen
      Karcher in the introduction of his I Ching translation <i>"Total
        Yijing"</i>. There are four categories in total listed below.
      When activated they will be added to the bottom of each reading
      page.<br>
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
